  At the high end game melee classes can get a direct upgrade to their characters by getting a new weaon or armor, and rightfully so, it is their job to be on the front line taking hits and dealing damage. Well, casters also get an upgrade if they get a new piece of gear as well. That is all well and good, but they are not out there fighting (normally).<br>
  The casters upgrades are in their spells. SO how great is it that they are going to balance us casters by giving us new uber spells when HALF OF US DO NOT HAVE THE ALREADY UBER RARE SPELLS THAT DROP IN THE GAME NOW!!!!!!!!!!!<br>
Spells are our life, yet over half of the 50+ spells for each class are npc drops. And half of those are rare as hell.<br>
How many druids are still looking for the 55 spell girdle of Karana, much less rotg and potg???<br>
How many clerics are still looking for aego/group aego, mark of karn???<br>
How many chanters are deperately seeking koadics???<br>
My point is, a melee continues to grow in strength when he levels in a direct way..more HP, more attack, more disciples. So even if he is using the same weapon, he is using it better and more effectively.<br>
Whereas a caster, if he dings and does not have any of the next level spells except for maybe the ONE that is purchaseable, has no noticeable upgrade except a few more hp's and maybe fewer resists.<br>
Yeah i know that the spell drops have supposedly increased, but i have yet to see it really hit the market.....we'll see i suppose.<br>
Anyway, ancient spells that are very rare is a neat idea, but just make sure the very rare spells we are all still missing that are currently in the game are a little more ummmmm available.<br>
<br>
Note this is not meant as a pissin contest between melee and casters at the high end. It is simply an observation on the existing state of affairs for spellcasters and their spells that already exist. Why would VI think we should get all excited over some Super Duper Ridiculous Rare Spell of Mob Slaying That You Will Never See, when alot of us have trouble gettin The Super Rare Spell That Would Have Been Handy For the Last Two Levels And You Still Don't Have.<br>
